OL,7,FWales have lost 17 successive Tests
OL,8,Fstretching back to the 2023 World Cup,
OL,9,Fwhile Warren Gatland departed as head
OL,10,Fcoach following a 22-15 defeat against
OL,11,FItaly in February.
OL,13,FCardiff boss Matt Sherratt took charge
OL,14,Fon an interim basis for Wales' three
OL,15,Fremaining Six Nations fixtures, and
OL,16,Foversaw a revival in terms of
OL,17,Fperformance until England travelled to
OL,18,FCardiff in the championship's final
OL,19,Fround and won 68-14.
